        <li>decentExtra-> but is often hard to follow</li>
        <li>decentExtra-> but is riddled with self-contradictions</li>
        <li>decentExtra-> but lacks any deep emotional appeal</li>
        <li>decentExtra-> but it is filled with strawmen and obviously fake stereotypes</li>
        <li>decentExtra-> but the author constantly uses words inappropriately in an attempt to sound smart</li>
        <li>decentExtra-> but it is obviously meant for an audience whose lifeways are unimaginably different from anything on the rim</li>
        <li>decentExtra-> but the writing is excessively flowery</li>
        <li>decentExtra-> but many of the passages are unnecessary and don't relate to the ideoligion in any way</li>

        <li>awfulDesc->very poorly written</li>
        <li>awfulDesc->terribly written</li>
        <li>awfulDesc->hard to read</li>
        <li>awfulDesc->hard to follow</li>
        <li>awfulDesc->fails to understand the ideoligion</li>
        <li>awfulDesc->filled with self-contradictions and undefined concepts</li>
        <li>awfulDesc->dominated by the author's own narcissism and savior complex</li>
        <li>awfulDesc->so indiosyncratic that no two readers can agree on what it's even describing</li>
        <li>awfulDesc->far, far too repetitive, long, and repetitive</li>
        <li>awfulExtra-> and the writing has clearly been edited over in parts by the contradicting beliefs of a different sect</li>
        <li>awfulExtra-> and is extremely hard to follow</li>
        <li>awfulExtra-> and fails to assemble a coherent picture of the ideoligion</li>
        <li>awfulExtra-> and lacks any sense of meaning or relevance</li>
        <li>awfulExtra-> and doesn't present any interesting ideas at all</li>
        <li>awfulExtra-> and fills the reader with ennui and boredom</li>
